Connecting to your creativity, instruments, and our family of artists has been the driving force behind our #vfConnected initiative and since the release of our global #vfConnected performance, we couldn't be more blown away by the level of creativity, passion, and performance demonstrated in every submission. Here are just a handful of the phenomenal performances you've submitted now featured alongside our family of artists. 👏 

#vfConnected Featured Players:
Michael Seyfried @michael.seyfried.music 
Mathieu Dinan @mathieudinan 
Guy Nwogang  @nwogang 
Dylan Galvan @dylan._drums 
Alfonso Mocerino @alfonsomocerino 
"A-Team Drumline" @a_team_drumline_library 
William Brown @williambrownpercussion 

You can watch their individual performances on our site along with all the other amazing submissions.
Stay tuned for more #vfConnected moments coming soon! 

Join VF Connected by:
1) Downloading the play-along tracks and sheet music for your instrument
2) Recording your performance
3) Uploading your video through our site for a chance to be featured alongside our Vic Firth family of artists!
Please include your name, email, and social media handles.

Composer: @iangrom_music

Our goal at Vic Firth is to build connection… connection between you and your instrument, between you and your music, between you and your audience, between you and the entire percussion community. Whether you’re sitting on the throne behind a drum kit, standing at the ready behind a marching snare, or ready for your cue behind a set of vibes or marimba, we want to help you stay connected to your craft. When you have the right tools, YOUR perfect pair, you feel a freedom to create, you feel ready to connect, and you can truly be in the moment.

Let’s celebrate these connections with the start of VF Connected, a musical chain performance that brings together artists from across genres, instruments, and continents. Collaborate with Vic Firth Family in an artfully crafted composition by Vic Firth Signature Artist, Ian Grom. VF Connected also features Mark Lettieri on guitar, and Joe Cleveland on bass. 

Join the jam, with downloadable tracks and resources here: https://vicfirth.zildjian.com/vfconnected

Submit your video through our site for a chance to be featured along with our family of artists! 

#vfConnected Featured Artists: 
Composer: 
~ @iangrom_music 

Drumset: 
~ @officialdaveweckl 
~ @juancarlitomendoza 
~ @nellibub 
~ @stixxtaylor 

Vibraphone: 
~ @anders_astrand 
~ @nathanskinnermusic 

Marimba: 
~ @jihyepercussion 
~ Se-Mi Hwang 

Marching Snare: 
~ @rogercarterdrums 

Join Vic Firth Connected by: 
1) Downloading the play-along tracks and sheet music for your instrument here vicfirth.com/vfconnected 
2) Recording your performance 
3) Uploading your video at vicfirth.com/vfconnected for a chance to be featured alongside our Vic Firth family of artists! 
Please include your name, email, and social media handles.

Check out Vic Firth on social media and #vfconnected for the latest on all things Vic Firth.

If you've been missing the sounds of drumline then we've got a special treat for you! The students and staff of the 2020 @wcu_drumline are proud to present their 2020 production entitled: “UNINVITED” 

WCU’s Gold Drumline, Front Ensemble, and Rhythm Section were able to piece together a two-minute production entiteled "Uninvited". An arrangement of “Uninvited” by Alanis Morissette, and the masterful work of “Shatter Me” by Lindsey Stirling. With no pre-camps, no band camp, and only two short rehearsals per week, the membership unified to defy the odds and make music together nonetheless.

Please join us in welcoming @linaanderberg to the Vic Firth Family! 👏

Lina is a professional drummer, based out of Sweden. With no musical background growing up, Lina’s drumming journey began as an “accident” when she tried the drums and was quickly hooked! She then pursued everything she could to build her drumming career. Since graduating from one of the best music schools in 2016, she has been working with many artists, performing for thousands of people at some of the biggest venues and festivals in Sweden. She continues to perform on various television shows and collaborates with many artists across the industry. 

🥢 Lina’s go-to sticks are the American Classic 5A’s.

“It's all about how the stick connects with my hands, the balanced weight, it just feels right. I’ve played Vic firth from the start, because it’s truly my perfect pair.”

Thank You Lina! And Welcome To The Family! 👏

#VicFirth #Drumsticks #VicFirthFamily #MyPerfectPair

Please join us in welcoming @raghavdrummer to the Vic Firth Family! 👏

Raghav is a virtuoso drummer who started at a young age of 3. Even at an early stage in his musical journey he amazed all at his sense of rhythm and feel on the drums. After many countless hours of playing live music across genres with the local School of Rock program, he was fortunate to be hired as a principal character in Sir Andrew Lloyd Webber's Tony-nominated School of Rock, the musical on Broadway where he performed for over 500 shows in the span of 18 months. 

Raghav has since developed his unique voice on the drums through his musicality and creativity and has a dedicated following on social media where he posts short clips of what he is working on and inspires many others to create alongside him.

🥢 Raghav's go-to sticks are the American Classic 5A's, SD2 Bolero, and the REMIX Brushes. 

"5A's have always felt the best for me. They have a perfect balance and consistency that help me bring out my unique touch irrespective of the kind of music I am playing." ~ Raghav 

Thank You Raghav! And Welcome To The Family! 👏
